, which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert DE LORE was born in 1250, in France, his father, André LEROUX, was 30 and his mother, Eustachie, was 25. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1250–":"1250–Surnud","1243–Female":"1243–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1225":"1225","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1250–":"1250–Kuollut","1243–Female":"1243–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1250–":"1250–Décédé","1243–Female":"1243–Décédée","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1280–Male":"1280–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","1225":"1225","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert DE LORE est né en 1250, à France, son père, André LEROUX, avait 30 ans et sa mère, Eustachie, avait 25 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1250–":"1250–Verstorben","1243–Female":"1243–Verstorben","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","1280–Male":"1280–Verstorben","1220–Male":"1220–Verstorben","1225–Female":"1225–Verstorben","1225":"1225","1245":"1245","1243":"1243","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Als Robert DE LOR